==English==
===Proper Noun===
'''Brandon'''
# an [[English]] [[habitational]] [[surname]] from any of several places of that name
# an [[Irish]] [[patronymic]] surname from the [[Gaelic]] ''Mac Breandáin''
# an [[American]] male [[given name]] derived from the surname
# from a surname which was derived from a place name meaning "hill covered with broom" in Old English. It is sometimes also used as a variant of [[Brendan]].